text: Maureen Theresa Muth "Rene" Portland (March 31, 1953 - July 22, 2018) was an American former head coach in women's college basketball. She was known for her 27-year career with the Penn State Nittany Lions basketball team. Her career includes 21 NCAA tournament appearances including a Final Four appearance in 2000. She was born in Broomall, Pennsylvania. Portland was one of a few women's basketball coaches to have won 600 or more games at a single school, with a career record of 606â€“236 at Penn State. Portland died in Tannersville, Pennsylvania following a three year battle with peritoneal cancer on July 22, 2018, aged 65. ==References== Category:1953 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Deaths from peritoneal cancer Category:Cancer deaths in Pennsylvania Category:Sportspeople from Pennsylvania
